==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Man-eater
<hw>Man"-eat`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One who, or that which, has an appetite for human flesh;
specifically, one of certain large sharks (esp. <spn>Carcharodon
carcharias</spn> syn. <spn>Carcharodon Rondeleti</spn>); also, a lion or
a tiger which has acquired the habit of feeding upon human
flesh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>man-eating shark</ent>⟦br⟧
